The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Australia, SA post easy wins
Dhaka: Australia and South Africa posted easy wins, but the West Indies had to toil hard to get the better of Ireland in their first league match of the ICC under-19 World Cup on Monday. In Rajsahi, defending champion Australia beat Canada by six wickets. Put in to bat, Canada were bowled out for 164 in 45.1 overs. Australia raced to the target losing four wickets in just 28.4 overs. T. Doropoulos hit 57. In Chittagong, South Africa won by eight wickets against Uganda. Uganda were all out for 125. South Africa reached the target comfortably for the loss of two wickets. The West Indies, however, struggled to a six-run win against Ireland in Khulna. Ireland scored 259 for nine in reply to West Indies 265 for eight.  BRIEF SCORES Canada 164 in 45.1 ovs (S. Anjaria 50; Coyte  3/42). Australia 165/4 in 28.4 ovs (T. Doropoulos  57). Australia won by 6 wkts.  Uganda 125 in 48.4 ovs  (September 4/14). South Africa 126/2 in 28 ovs (A.  Birch 56 n.o.). South Africa won by 8 wkts. West Indies 265/8 in 50  ovs (X. Marshall 83; Thompson 5/49). Ireland 259/9  in 50 ovs (K OBrien 95). West Indies won by 6 runs.  (AP)  Copyright 
